# AI Bot Rules

## AWS Bedrock Integration
- Use `@aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime` with Converse API
- Support models: `anthropic.claude-sonnet`, `amazon.nova-pro`, `meta.llama3`, `mistralai.mistral`
- Use streaming via `ConverseStreamCommand` for real-time responses
- Per-company Bedrock config (endpoint, region) from Company entity

## Bot Entity Pattern
- Each bot belongs to a company
- System prompt defines bot personality and capabilities
- Model, temperature, maxTokens are configurable per bot
- Tools array defines what actions the bot can perform

## Bot Task Processing
- When a message @mentions a bot, create a BotTask record
- Queue task in Bull queue with `botId`, `chatId`, `triggerMessageId`
- Worker picks up task, invokes Bedrock with conversation context
- Stream response chunks back via WebSocket `bot:response` event
- On completion, save full response and update BotTask status

## Bot Messages
- Messages from bots have `senderType: 'bot'` and `senderId: botId`
- Bot response messages use type `botResult`
- Frontend renders bot messages with distinct styling (AI badge, colored border)
- Rich cards for structured data (markdown rendered, collapsible sections)

## Security
- Only company admins can create/configure/delete bots
- Bot access to Bedrock uses company's AWS credentials
- All bot tasks are logged for audit (tokens, duration, cost)
- Rate limit bot invocations per company
